Presets Overview
Presets combine multiple base animations for common effects. They often have size variants (sm, md, lg).
* Fades: motion-preset-fade
* Slides: motion-preset-slide-right, motion-preset-slide-left, motion-preset-slide-up, motion-preset-slide-down, motion-preset-slide-up-right, etc.
* Focus: motion-preset-focus
* Blur with Movement: motion-preset-blur-right, motion-preset-blur-left, etc.
* Rebound: motion-preset-rebound (with direction: right, left, up, down)
* Bounce: motion-preset-bounce
* Expand/Shrink: motion-preset-expand, motion-preset-shrink
* Pop/Compress: motion-preset-pop, motion-preset-compress
* Shake/Wiggle: motion-preset-shake, motion-preset-wiggle
* Confetti: motion-preset-confetti (a complex, pre-built animation)
* Pulse/Wobble/Seesaw/Oscillate/Stretch/Float: motion-preset-pulse, motion-preset-wobble, etc. (looping animations)
* Spin: motion-preset-spin (continuous rotation)
* Blink: motion-preset-blink (looping opacity change)
* Typewriter: motion-preset-typewriter-[20] (animates text appearing as if typed; value is the number of characters)
